   <mods:abstract>Lists miscellaneous expenditures totaling 53/19/6, pounds such as payment
            for a blank book, for binding two books, for a trunk to carry papers to Hartford (13
            shillings sixpence); for a chest to carry the papers from Hartford, the trunk having
            broken on the journey (one pound ten shillings); for clerks, and room, fire, and candle
            for them for nearly two months (two pounds); for Jay's own journey to Hartford at one
            pound eight shillings a day (22 pounds 8 shillings).One sheet in another hand lists
            payment due to Jay for his work for 153 days from 18 July to 20 December 1769 at 20
            shillings a day, and for 96 days at 28shillings a day. In Jay's hand, this is corrected
            to 155 days at 20 shillings a day. Arithmetical jottings in Jay's hand check the amount
            still owed to him. Evidently he had been paid for 80 days at 28 shillings a day, and 43
            pounds was still due to him. Mostly in Jay's hand.</mods:abstract>
